This is not La Giralda .. and we are not in Spain!
This "Al-Nasser Qalawoon" Minaret was built on the Andalusian style.
It was built in the year 1285 AD by Sultan "Al-Nasser Qalawoon" as part of his Complex and was restored by his son in the year 1303 AD after hit by an earthquake in 1302! 🕌
It consists of three floors of which a third the dates back to the restoration period.
In this photo and to the right, the wall of the mausoleum of both Qalawwon and his son Mohammad and to the left a wall from Mohammad's Madrasa!
📍Qalawoon Complex, al-Muizz L'din Allah Street, Cairo
